This tells us that something has written a zero byte into free memory at
location @samp{0x08067FF6}.  Unfortunately, the library only caught it at the
next call to one of its functions so it had already happened somewhere in
between the last call and the current call.  Turning on the @option{LOGALL}
option in the @env{MPATROL_OPTIONS} environment variable allows us to see the
last successful function call to the mpatrol library.

